### **Titan has been shutdown**

# ![][image1]2024 Tokamak Network(TON) Bi-Weekly Report \#26 : 12/17 \~ 12/30

### Highlight

Titan has been shut down. We will finalize the claimable L2 asset list by January 3, 2024\. The L1 claim feature via the Tokamak Bridge will become available on January 6, 2025\. All relevant contract’s admin rights related to Titan will be removed to prevent any abuse in the future, before the end of 2025\. For more details, please visit \[[link](https://medium.com/tokamak-network/tokamak-network-to-sunset-titan-b4471019c92)\].

1. **Grant program**: create your own project and apply for [GranTON](https://www.notion.so/Tokamak-Network-Grant-Program-GranTON-f2384b458ea341a0987c7e73a909aa21?pvs=4)  
2. **Full time**: [apply for a full-time position](https://recruit.wanted.co.kr/p/QVxQS0MVRm5HWEpb) and earn salary in USDT/USDC in addition to the [TON](https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/tokamak-network) grant from the project.  
3. **Part time**: apply for a part-time by earning [TON](https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/tokamak-network) as a grant from project. Please contact the [project leader (owner)](https://www.notion.so/Tokamak-Network-Onboarding-523bc627bd374326b5dfbec3d3b0a8e1?pvs=21) directly and discuss with them.

* **Why is the market cap different for each site?**

The market cap on platforms such as CoinMarketCap and CoinGecko is calculated using their respective methodologies. We are currently in communication with each platform to address this discrepancy. For the most accurate market cap, please refer to the Bi-Weekly Report or the official site: [https://price.tokamak.network/](https://price.tokamak.network/).

* **Please tell me about the TON issuance.**

Seigniorage (additional issuance) is a mechanism that applies only to users who have purchased and staked TON, and it is conducted under specific conditions. The newly issued TON is distributed as staked TON, and those who receive it must wait at least two weeks before they can sell.

The TON seigniorage model has been in place since the inception of TON tokenomics. While it is difficult to alter the issuance amount, the staking rewards for stakers can be adjusted. However, reducing the staking rewards may decrease benefits for existing TON holders, leading to more TON being sold on the market, which can drive prices down. Conversely, increasing staking rewards could reduce the circulating TON supply in the market and potentially support price increases.
